HEADWORD: yin and yang
<hw>yin and yang</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chinese
philosophy)</fld> <def>the two fundamental principles, one negative,
dark, passive, cold, wet, and feminine (yin) and the other (yang)
positive, bright, active, dry, hot and masculine. The interactions and
balance of these forces in people and nature influence their behavior
and fate.</def> <au>[RHUD]</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

